00:24:05,736 --> 00:24:14,925
So this all white and cozy feelings came right before the final level. Our main character

229
00:24:15,105 --> 00:24:22,853
finally faced her own issues. We're portraying a breakdown, the absolute feeling of being completely

230
00:24:22,933 --> 00:24:23,713
alone and numb.

231
00:24:24,732 --> 00:24:31,017
It was clear I wanted to have it as dark and black as possible.

232
00:24:31,077 --> 00:24:32,598
No colors, dense fog.

233
00:24:33,399 --> 00:24:36,321
So I hope you can see anything here.

234
00:24:37,522 --> 00:24:43,067
In general, we had many issues with our main color, black, in the game.

235
00:24:43,207 --> 00:24:52,114
How dark can you turn the game before it becomes hard to watch or understand where you are?

236
00:24:53,285 --> 00:25:01,451
A huge issue is the many different monitors we needed to adjust the game colors to.

237
00:25:01,931 --> 00:25:08,715
I always wanted to go as dark as possible, but when we tested the game on another PC,

238
00:25:08,795 --> 00:25:11,357
it was often like simply pitch black.

239
00:25:12,558 --> 00:25:18,142
We prevented total navigational loss of the player by adding two thick.

240
00:25:18,844 --> 00:25:29,453
One was a subtle light source around K, so the player could always see what is around them.

241
00:25:29,633 --> 00:25:36,519
The second important help was again to make the background fog lighter than the fog close by,

242
00:25:36,539 --> 00:25:41,303
so you have the silhouette. With that you can always see like this silhouette of the

243
00:25:43,627 --> 00:25:52,622
clearing which functions as landmarks. With those tricks I could finally have my

244
00:25:53,796 --> 00:26:01,640
pitch black parts to. So one of the biggest challenges when we created

245
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:10,585
Tea of Solitude had been our manpower. Creating a game of that size with a team of 12

246
00:26:11,665 --> 00:26:15,547
made us come up with a unique design process.

247
00:26:17,455 --> 00:26:25,559
As I mentioned before, I had been not only the art director, but also the brighter main game designer,

248
00:26:25,659 --> 00:26:32,742
had with the level design, did the level design schedules, and did the level art with one other

249
00:26:32,922 --> 00:26:39,625
level artist beside, and had other responsibilities like the company had.

250
00:26:40,065 --> 00:26:46,148
So in the first years of the concept phase, I just had one program helping me with like

251
00:26:47,158 --> 00:26:53,721
Sea of Solitude and we needed to work on other games too that kept the company afloat while

252
00:26:53,762 --> 00:26:59,765
we were finding the right approach for Sea of Solitude. So it was like a really just two people

253
00:26:59,805 --> 00:27:08,650
team at the beginning, me and one programmer. So I basically just had time to do one key artwork.

254
00:27:09,350 --> 00:27:12,092
for the environment art at the beginning.

255
00:27:12,112 --> 00:27:17,415
So I did it in my favorite 2D tool, like Photoshop,

256
00:27:17,816 --> 00:27:18,736
Adobe Photoshop.

257
00:27:19,437 --> 00:27:22,579
I usually work with like many layers in Photoshop

258
00:27:22,659 --> 00:27:26,482
and often use like the so-called blending modes

259
00:27:27,022 --> 00:27:31,866
for those layers, like multiply, like overlay and transparency.

260
00:27:31,946 --> 00:27:34,147
I use transparency, gradients and masks.

261
00:27:34,548 --> 00:27:37,230
I love using all this for my style.

262
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:48,688
So when I finished that one key artwork, I walked up to my one programmer and showed him exactly

263
00:27:49,068 --> 00:27:56,113
how I made this key artwork in Photoshop and asked him if he can reproduce

264
00:27:57,334 --> 00:28:01,617
this immunity as a tool for 3D environment.

265
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:09,604
so that he creates something in unity that I can work the same way I would work in 2D photoshop.

266
00:28:11,565 --> 00:28:19,309
Because of the tiny team size, we early on decided to not use any textures

267
00:28:21,311 --> 00:28:28,875
in the environment. So even like cracks on the wall and the leaves are triangles.

268
00:28:29,569 --> 00:28:36,493
and that had been a huge advantage as we didn't need to unwrap anything or texture,

269
00:28:36,933 --> 00:28:46,758
we could scale and squeeze the models freely. We also didn't need to spend time creating textures

270
00:28:47,738 --> 00:28:55,902
as mentioned and because of this we could build almost a whole city district, like a real whole

271
00:28:56,343 --> 00:28:57,663
city district was just.

272
00:28:59,196 --> 00:29:09,224
one environment artist needs. So to bring life to the

273
00:29:09,645 --> 00:29:17,711
untextual environment, I asked my programmer for various tools to help me. Coloring the shadow

274
00:29:18,852 --> 00:29:24,557
and ambient occlusion was really important that I could like really color it however I want.

275
00:29:26,114 --> 00:29:35,437
We also misused the specular component of the materials in Unity and used just slightly

276
00:29:35,537 --> 00:29:39,519
different colors within this specular gradient.

277
00:29:39,559 --> 00:29:46,982
So when you move through the world of SOS, this effect brings more life into the world

278
00:29:47,062 --> 00:29:49,162
without you really noticing it.

279
00:29:49,783 --> 00:29:51,683
It makes SOS look less blunt.

280
00:29:53,063 --> 00:29:57,886
That was a really cool check, I feel.

281
00:30:00,408 --> 00:30:03,410
So, I used the gradient.

282
00:30:04,147 --> 00:30:10,072
in Photoshop create like distance fog and also ground fog like for this concept art I did.

283
00:30:10,472 --> 00:30:18,659
So the specialty in SOS had been that I needed fog over and under water but the fog over water

284
00:30:19,219 --> 00:30:25,765
shouldn't affect everything underwater and vice versa. So our programmer Dirk

285
00:30:26,438 --> 00:30:31,403
step by step built me a Vasa system tool in Unity,

286
00:30:31,823 --> 00:30:36,187
where I could almost use the same workflow

287
00:30:36,327 --> 00:30:37,328
I had in Photoshop.

288
00:30:38,930 --> 00:30:39,530
With that...

289
00:30:40,357 --> 00:30:48,740
I didn't need to spend time painting artworks, but I could directly build a one-to-one example for

290
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:55,102
my whole team, where they didn't need to interpret my drawings, but could see like the final product

291
00:30:55,743 --> 00:31:01,525
and use that as a blueprint for everything they needed to create and see of Solitude.

292
00:31:02,345 --> 00:31:05,847
So remember, we were only 12 people, we need to iterate fast.

293
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:16,848
And if you do the same, I advise you to build tools that makes you as flexible as possible.

294
00:31:19,290 --> 00:31:25,616
So that brings me to the second biggest art direction aspect next to the environment art,

295
00:31:25,816 --> 00:31:33,223
the monster design. In general, we have two different types of monsters.

296
00:31:34,219 --> 00:31:40,364
in SOS, K's monsters and the monsters of the family of K.

297
00:31:41,345 --> 00:31:48,991
All of them are based on the human behind it, mixed with the biggest emotion they have.

298
00:31:49,651 --> 00:31:52,734
These aspects manifest into their monster form.

299
00:31:57,807 --> 00:32:05,291
When I did the very first sketch of Monsters in Sea of Solitude, I sat down in front of a blank paper

300
00:32:05,892 --> 00:32:16,778
and I imagined how I would feel when I'm at the absolute lowest point, like angry and sad.

301
00:32:17,158 --> 00:32:23,482
So I rather scratched over the paper and then drawing anything particular.

302
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:28,661
and a black ball of lines came out of the session.

303
00:32:29,201 --> 00:32:33,602
So I started to bring this basic idea

304
00:32:33,822 --> 00:32:37,723
of how manifested anger and sadness could look like

305
00:32:38,243 --> 00:32:40,104
into a human form.

306
00:32:41,404 --> 00:32:45,425
While doing so, the wired lines

307
00:32:45,465 --> 00:32:47,646
turned slowly into a feathery fur.

308
00:32:49,889 --> 00:32:56,472
Then I imagined that in order to still go on in life, not giving up,

309
00:32:57,393 --> 00:33:07,478
even though you go through all these hardships, you need to still have a flame of hope burning inside you.

310
00:33:08,215 --> 00:33:19,661
So I drew this monster with red, orange light shining from the inside out

311
00:33:20,201 --> 00:33:26,744
and through their mouth and through their eyes. This is the base of all monsters you

312
00:33:26,844 --> 00:33:32,506
encounter in the game. A black appearance with red shining eyes and mouth.

313
00:33:33,622 --> 00:33:38,264
A short comment before I go deeper into the family monster designs.

314
00:33:39,545 --> 00:33:48,090
The stories about the parents and about the brother are not taken from my life.

315
00:33:48,570 --> 00:33:55,094
I have no brother and my parents are now happily married for over 40 years.

316
00:33:56,435 --> 00:33:56,815
40 years.

317
00:33:57,816 --> 00:34:00,938
So those stories are inspired by colleagues and friends.

318
00:34:02,537 --> 00:34:10,324
The brother monster had been the first family monster I did a concept art of.

319
00:34:10,865 --> 00:34:20,033
The brother gets bullied in school by his former friends and he suffers from harsh self-doubt.

320
00:34:20,393 --> 00:34:26,459
Like unsure for a long time if he is a problem in this whole issue.

321
00:34:27,500 --> 00:34:32,442
So the longer he is in this situation, the stronger his buddhies are harassing him.

322
00:34:33,463 --> 00:34:45,729
The first of the strongest emotions he has is this urge to just want to fly away from this situation.

323
00:34:46,210 --> 00:34:52,353
Like the birds he used to watch through the school windows during lessons.

324
00:34:53,699 --> 00:35:03,882
This is why his monster version appears like a huge bird, in particular a raven mixed with a human body.

325
00:35:06,142 --> 00:35:13,804
He is constantly surrounded by his own weather, which reflects his emotions too.

326
00:35:14,425 --> 00:35:21,486
The second emotion next to the urge to fly away is fear to be seen.

327
00:35:22,612 --> 00:35:28,314
He wants to hide because his buddies start harassing him as soon as they see him.

328
00:35:29,575 --> 00:35:37,498
So I created a thick fog around him, almost colorless, where he hides inside.

329
00:35:38,418 --> 00:35:46,061
His water is special, as it is the only one where you can instantly die.

330
00:35:47,026 --> 00:35:52,449
As mentioned before, the water stands for the ocean of tears, desperation, sadness.

331
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:59,694
So his emotional state is already so bad that we decided to make his water deadly.

332
00:36:00,554 --> 00:36:08,039
When Kay falls into that water, hands of the Buddhists obstruct, grab her and drown her.

333
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:11,201
The father of Kay,

334
00:36:17,022 --> 00:36:21,426
to leave his wife, as they married rather early

335
00:36:21,766 --> 00:36:24,690
in their life and just grew apart.

336
00:36:25,510 --> 00:36:29,334
They tried over many years to fix the marriage,

337
00:36:30,455 --> 00:36:33,679
but sometimes it just didn't work out.

338
00:36:34,299 --> 00:36:38,524
And the longer they tried, the unhealthier

339
00:36:38,544 --> 00:36:39,845
the whole situation became.

340
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:49,644
As he, the father, struggles to openly tell his wife what he feels and rather avoid confrontation,

341
00:36:50,145 --> 00:37:00,531
he starts hiding from her by working way too much. So I drew his monster version as a big chameleon

342
00:37:00,691 --> 00:37:08,375
mixed with a human. I wanted to show with little details like that he is still wearing his wedding

343
00:37:08,455 --> 00:37:08,655
ring.

344
00:37:09,958 --> 00:37:15,321
even as a monster that he loves his family.

345
00:37:16,601 --> 00:37:20,243
We encounter him first on the skyscraper

346
00:37:20,344 --> 00:37:21,884
where his office is.

347
00:37:22,545 --> 00:37:25,426
I wondered that the building looks almost destroyed.

348
00:37:26,027 --> 00:37:28,408
The father monster and the mother monster

349
00:37:28,828 --> 00:37:30,749
fighting for a long while already.

350
00:37:31,330 --> 00:37:34,472
She tried to get him out of the skyscrapers

351
00:37:34,812 --> 00:37:37,433
and with this, she destroyed it almost.

352
00:37:39,450 --> 00:37:46,995
Also, I designed the interior of the building, or I had the idea for the design of the interior

353
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:54,900
building as rather empty and cold. Same as the father feels. He sits on top of the building,

354
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:57,301
angrily, angrily crying out.

355
00:37:57,890 --> 00:38:07,317
His screams produce steam streams that comes out of every vent inside the skyscraper and

356
00:38:07,417 --> 00:38:09,818
push K, the player, away.

357
00:38:11,219 --> 00:38:17,503
The father monster tries to avoid touching the water, the ocean of tears, like the plaque,

358
00:38:18,104 --> 00:38:23,407
as he is unwilling to really deal with his own issues.

359
00:38:23,927 --> 00:38:25,208
He can't even swim.

360
00:38:26,469 --> 00:38:27,390
The mother monster

361
00:38:28,464 --> 00:38:34,346
looks like a giant octopus mixed with a female head.

362
00:38:34,366 --> 00:38:40,208
She is about 10 times a lot bigger than the father monster.

363
00:38:41,848 --> 00:38:46,929
I imagined like a loving mother that desperately tries

364
00:38:47,310 --> 00:38:50,070
to hold the families, the whole family together,

365
00:38:50,830 --> 00:38:53,631
tries to hold onto like everything

366
00:38:54,391 --> 00:38:56,832
and keep it from crumbling apart.

367
00:38:57,812 --> 00:39:02,655
So she needed many arms and I immediately thought of an octopus.

368
00:39:03,976 --> 00:39:12,661
The mother monster is often completely underwater and that means that she is constantly worrying

369
00:39:12,821 --> 00:39:20,026
and sad but as soon as her daughter or husband shows up she comes out of the water and at least

370
00:39:20,106 --> 00:39:27,210
try to appear confident. The mother monster and father monster share a huge

371
00:39:27,660 --> 00:39:35,943
weather surrounding them. So we have this dramatic like red and orange colors throughout most of their

372
00:39:36,063 --> 00:39:42,825
level. It stands for the end of their partnership but also the heat of tension surrounding them.

373
00:39:43,666 --> 00:39:51,248
The water level is much higher than in the brother's level beforehand as both like the

374
00:39:51,288 --> 00:39:57,450
mother and the father suffer from a profound loneliness within their relationship.

375
00:39:58,023 --> 00:40:02,144
that affects the whole family, including their children.

376
00:40:03,044 --> 00:40:05,705
The final argument those two have

377
00:40:06,165 --> 00:40:10,046
in the destroyed version of the home in the game,

378
00:40:11,146 --> 00:40:12,947
it looks like a bombed crater.

379
00:40:13,067 --> 00:40:16,527
I hope you can see that in the concept.

380
00:40:18,168 --> 00:40:23,269
When the player comes to the home at first, it's still intact.

381
00:40:23,989 --> 00:40:32,436
and it's also the only place next to the end of the game where you see plants and vegetation,

382
00:40:32,937 --> 00:40:44,286
plants and vegetation in general. It stands for that Kay feels most healthy there at her home,

383
00:40:45,247 --> 00:40:52,213
so she can see the life which she can't throughout most of the game.

384
00:40:52,715 --> 00:40:53,856
So you can see it there.

385
00:40:56,117 --> 00:41:04,643
So the monster, the boyfriend monster, is the most unique one of all family monsters.

386
00:41:05,304 --> 00:41:10,647
Kay's boyfriend suffers from depression, but tries to appear fine to the outside.

387
00:41:11,007 --> 00:41:20,254
He is doing pretty well until he falls in love with Kay and is finally forced to open up about his struggles.

388
00:41:21,135 --> 00:41:28,140
So when we meet the boyfriend monster first, he appears like a shiny white wolf, like white

389
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:29,000
lone wolf.

390
00:41:29,441 --> 00:41:34,063
Throughout the development, the whole development of Sea of Solitude, I educate myself about

391
00:41:34,103 --> 00:41:40,627
mental health a lot, but also about metaphors, symbols, and so on.

392
00:41:41,168 --> 00:41:47,972
The lone wolf is a typical symbol for a man that tends to act independently and spend

393
00:41:48,072 --> 00:41:50,133
more time alone than in groups.

394
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:55,464
And it is not only him I portray shiny and white.

395
00:41:56,044 --> 00:41:59,527
In his level, the whole Berlin district

396
00:41:59,988 --> 00:42:03,371
where SOS takes place is snowed in.

397
00:42:04,111 --> 00:42:06,213
And he is like really, really good

398
00:42:06,273 --> 00:42:08,175
at camouflaging his real feelings.

399
00:42:08,215 --> 00:42:13,099
So he put the whole game under a cozy white snow layer.

400
00:42:14,859 --> 00:42:20,383
So every time he interacts with Kay in the game and she touches him,

401
00:42:20,883 --> 00:42:29,029
part of his white perfect camouflage falls off and we see the black dog beneath it,

402
00:42:29,189 --> 00:42:38,976
which is a known metaphor for depression. I again designed him part human and part animal.

403
00:42:41,498 --> 00:42:41,838
Kay.

404
00:42:43,100 --> 00:42:49,163
The main character itself, I wanted to portray in a different way.

405
00:42:49,183 --> 00:42:53,844
And as ripped apart into her basic emotions,

406
00:42:54,545 --> 00:42:57,226
all of these emotions coming to life.

407
00:42:57,826 --> 00:43:01,047
And she needs to interact with them throughout the entire game.

408
00:43:02,649 --> 00:43:11,673
I took her strongest emotions like self-doubt, joy, self-destruction, hope and willpower.

409
00:43:12,213 --> 00:43:15,855
The playable character represents willpower.

410
00:43:16,295 --> 00:43:23,218
She looks much more like a human than every other monster as she is the closest to recovery.

411
00:43:24,702 --> 00:43:32,489
But of course I wanted to design the main character more human, so the player can project

412
00:43:32,529 --> 00:43:33,530
themselves better onto it.

413
00:43:35,731 --> 00:43:42,197
Kay is actually completely naked, which was important to me to portray how vulnerable

414
00:43:42,257 --> 00:43:47,702
she is in the state of change and transition to a more healthy life.

415
00:43:48,262 --> 00:43:51,945
The only thing Kay wears is her backpack.

416
00:43:53,438 --> 00:43:58,300
It carries the baggage we all carry throughout our life.

417
00:43:59,040 --> 00:44:05,102
She doesn't know how to cope with all these emotions

418
00:44:05,662 --> 00:44:06,542
she's going through.

419
00:44:06,582 --> 00:44:10,944
So the backpack becomes bigger and bigger

420
00:44:10,964 --> 00:44:12,284
throughout the game.

421
00:44:13,222 --> 00:44:20,146
until it's like really huge and it bursts and forcing her to finally overcome her own struggles

422
00:44:20,306 --> 00:44:30,672
or all deal with all her emotions. Zeddout is the first other monster you meet, uh,

423
00:44:30,692 --> 00:44:35,535
you really interact with and meet in the game. Um, all of Kay's monsters are partly

424
00:44:36,193 --> 00:44:45,900
her human body. So self-doubt, I choose to mix her with like the human body and with a snail,

425
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:53,325
like especially with a shell. Self-doubt as an emotion always feels to me

426
00:44:54,765 --> 00:45:00,269
as it ends up trying to hide somewhere, like it's hiding, self-doubt and you hide.

427
00:45:01,447 --> 00:45:03,329
Mostly, of course, at home.

428
00:45:03,849 --> 00:45:07,712
So a snail shell is in their home.

429
00:45:09,654 --> 00:45:15,059
The self-doubt monster also has teeth like a small child.

430
00:45:15,859 --> 00:45:23,946
I wanted to show that what comes out of the mouth of self-doubt is nothing educated,

431
00:45:25,467 --> 00:45:27,789
but rather like blunt or warm.

432
00:45:29,448 --> 00:45:33,429
often true, but so more childlike.

433
00:45:33,469 --> 00:45:38,091
The self-doubt monster shrinks over the course of the game

434
00:45:38,511 --> 00:45:43,053
until she turns from self-doubt to healthy doubt.

435
00:45:43,913 --> 00:45:48,435
So first she is house high and super scary.

436
00:45:49,736 --> 00:45:52,497
So at the end of the game, Kay can't even take her

437
00:45:52,557 --> 00:45:55,118
in her arms, she's like a baby,

438
00:45:55,298 --> 00:45:58,039
that this healthy doubt incites.

439
00:46:00,682 --> 00:46:06,243
Self-destruction is a mixture between Kay and a siren and a shark.

440
00:46:06,544 --> 00:46:14,845
Like she tries to lurk Kay back into the water, into the ocean of tears so she can swallow Kay again.

441
00:46:15,525 --> 00:46:19,706
When I started scribbling her, she was rather soft at the beginning,

442
00:46:19,906 --> 00:46:27,068
self-destruction, and a whale, like a whale. But the more her role became clear,

443
00:46:27,508 --> 00:46:28,928
like the main antagonist.

444
00:46:29,683 --> 00:46:34,726
and the representation of self-destruction.

445
00:46:34,806 --> 00:46:39,368
She more turned into a super creepy being

446
00:46:40,148 --> 00:46:43,250
with this huge sharp teeth.

447
00:46:46,752 --> 00:46:50,494
Okay, so just her torso,

448
00:46:50,554 --> 00:46:52,915
yeah, just her torso and her eyes

449
00:46:53,475 --> 00:46:55,256
are in front of the head.

450
00:46:56,327 --> 00:47:01,611
and not on the side, reminds us that there is also some human part in it.

451
00:47:02,272 --> 00:47:05,154
If you look really closely, you can see that the feet

452
00:47:06,235 --> 00:47:11,059
of Kay's body meld together to form a fin in this monster.

453
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:14,762
She is always like underwater.

454
00:47:14,982 --> 00:47:17,645
The ocean of tears is her natural habitat.

455
00:47:18,546 --> 00:47:23,069
